node.title: Spain's La Palma volcano falls quiet after 85 days, but eruption may not be over
node.description: Tremors calm after nearly three months of constant roaring from a volcano that sent rivers of lava running through Spain’s Canary Islands, but experts warn it may not mean the eruption is nearing an end.

node.title: Sam Kerr and Ellie Carpenter short-listed for FIFPro's best XI
node.description: Selection in the World XI squad is considered one of football's highest honours as it is voted upon by the players themselves.

node.title: Covid-19 border restrictions exacerbating vet shortages in New Zealand
node.description: The Veterinary Council of New Zealand says it is taking a pragmatic approach as a regulator because the sector is feeling the pressure of the Covid-19 pandemic and staff shortages.

node.title: Canada offers billions to compensate indigenous children
node.description: Canada has pledged up to $C40 billion (approx $NZ46b) in compensation for indigenous children and families who suffered discrimination while in foster care.

node.title: Pfizer’s Covid Pill Works Well, Company Confirms in Final Analysis
node.description: The treatment, called Paxlovid, is likely to work against Omicron and could be available in the United States before the end of the year.

node.title: European Human Rights Court Urges Russia to Tackle 'Staggering Scale' of Domestic Violence
node.description: Russia to pay more than $500,000 to four survivors of domestic abuse after a court ruled the country is in violation of the European Convention on Human Rights.

node.title: Treasury to Release $8.7B for Lending to Smaller Communities, Minority-Owned Businesses
node.description: Vice President Kamala Harris and Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen announced the funds to be distributed to over 180 financial institutions across 36 states.

node.title: CNN Fires Producer John Griffin After He Is Accused of Grooming Girls for Sex
node.description: Griffin, 44, faces a minimum sentence of 10 years in prison up to life behind bars for each count, according to the Department of Justice.

node.title: Moms Say They Provide Most of the Care, Emotional Support for Their Kids: Poll
node.description: Americans without kids are more optimistic that they would share responsibilities equally with a partner compared with what parents report actually happens.

node.title: Demand for rapid antigen tests ramps up in Auckland as border reopens
node.description: The Ministry of Health has sent 250,000 tests to sites across the country, yet some in Auckland have told RNZ they've received only a small number or none at all and may have to turn people away.

node.title: The must-have app that tells you when the PS5 is back in stock
node.description: Popular services like HotStock, ZooLert and StockInformer promise to tell shoppers when they can buy scarce items. But they're not foolproof.

node.title: Dave Ramsey Fired Employee for Taking Covid Precautions, Suit Says
node.description: In his complaint, a former employee says the Tennessee radio broadcaster, an evangelical Christian who has built a personal finance empire, violated his religious rights.

node.title: Amtrak temporarily drops its vaccine mandate, avoiding cuts to service.
node.description: The shift in policy means that Amtrak officials no longer anticipate cuts to service next month.

node.title: Teen, 7-Year-Old Among Those Killed When Migrant Boat Capsized in English Channel
node.description: French authorities identified 26 people who died when a migrant boat sank between France and the U.K. last month.

node.title: Man Convicted of Killing Wife with Opioid-Laced Ice Cream to Obtain Insurance Payout
node.description: David Pettis gave his wife 10 times the amount of hydrocodone considered a "therapeutic dose" by crushing it up in her ice cream the night she died in 2018.

node.title: COVID cases in NSW reach three-month high after 1,360 new infections recorded
node.description: Health authorities in NSW confirm 1,360 cases of COVID-19 in the 24 hours to 8:00pm yesterday, as a cluster in Newcastle grows and the Premier delays a press conference on the virus.
